# GSD-2 runtime state (per-project, not shared).
# Exception: .gsd/deferred/ holds project-level design work preserved for
# resumption (plans, context, decision pointers). Deferred design work is
# institutional memory that would cost non-recoverable context if lost to
# machine loss; it is tracked in git. Agent-operational state (plans being
# actively edited, DB artifacts, rendered summaries of closed work) stays
# gitignored. D026 (pending — blocked on MCP-bridge bind issue; see
# .gsd/deferred/M005/upstream-issues/mcp-bridge-boolean-coercion.md)
# will capture the distinguishing principle formally once the tool unblocks.
# Using `.gsd/*` + `!.gsd/deferred/` because `.gsd/` as a directory-rule
# prevents any re-inclusion of contents via `!`.
.gsd/*
!.gsd/deferred/

